<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <title>CSS Test: width:auto and height:auto on single region box</title>
    <link rel="author" title="Vincent Hardy, Adobe Systems" href="mailto:vhardy@adobe.com" />
    <link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css3-regions/#rfcb-flow-fragment-height-resolution" />
    <link rel="match" href="regions-auto-size-1-ref.xht" />
    <meta name="flags" content="" />
    <meta name="assert" content=
    "The height of a region with height:auto is computed from the fragment content. Floats and relative positioned boxes are accounted for properly." />
<style>
    /*<![CDATA[*/
#region {
    border: 1px solid #a0a0a0;
    flow-from: article;
}

#article {
    flow-into: article;
}

.inline-box {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border: 1px solid #888;
    background: #aaa;
}

.floater {
    width: 50px;
    height: 50px;
    border: 1px solid #33a;
    background: #66e;
    float: left;
}

.offset {
    position: relative;
    top: 10px;
}

/*]]>*/
</style>
</head>
<body>
    <p>You should see a gray border box that that is as wide as the display area and tightly fits float blue blox but
        the relatively positioned gray box (rightmost) should overflow.</p>
    <div id="region"></div>
    <div id="article">
        <span class="inline-box"></span>
        <span class="inline-box"></span>
        <span class="inline-box offset"></span>
        <div class="floater"></div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>